</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I may have to quit EQ</span><hr size=1> I may have to give up EQ. For a change it isn't because I am bored with it, or that VI has upset me, or that my class sucks. I play a bard, and I feel that class is a great one, well balanced and very fun. Unfortunately, it can also be a painful class. Twisting songs has become close to impossible for me, due to the shooting pains that run up my arm. Sigh. A bard who can't twist songs, shouldn't play.<br>
<br>
I was getting to the part of the game to which I was always looking forward, namely the endgame of plane raids and epic encounters. I am sorry to say that I have never killed a dragon, nor a god. I will miss that.<br>
<br>
I am hopeful that I will be able to redesign my keyboard layout, and find a remedy for my arm. (Hey, if Def Leppard can have  one armed drummer, maybe I can be a one armed bard.) If so, and if it does not take to long, I look forward to seeing all my friends in EQ again. In the meantime, I am likely to be absent, although I still read the boards.<br>
<br>
Be safe everyone. It was good to meet ya all. <p>Ziktiny Totenstille<br>
51 Necromancer<br>
Retired<br>
