Rock on<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubrumfondl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>brumfondl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/14/01 12:38:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I may have to quit EQ</span><hr size=1> My keyboard and mousepad have wristrests because I started getting OOS. If you haven't already got some they may be a good first port of call. My problem was in my mouse hand and got to the point where I couldn't close my hand without pain. Now as long as I don't go totally overboard playing I am ok.<br>
