Hope this helps. <p><b>Brumfondl Majicthise</b><BR>
Daughter of Hatred<BR>
56th Level Servant of Rallos Zek<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upurifyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Purifyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.nuttysites.com/rodent/jyana1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1259<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/14/01 12:49:32 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> You need to start stretching every morning when you get up - or at least before you start playing - wrist and elbow stretches being the most important - I started to get those shooting pains as well a long while back and I hated the idea of having to give up EQ because of it - stretching works great tho when I remember to do it - and I play more EQ now than I did before - look for an ergonomics/carpal tunnel syndrome site or check a bookstore for info on stretching - some books have set plans with different levels corresponding for how much you use a computer - the vital aspect of all this is to ensure proper blood flow to your arms and hands - its when that blood flow is altered that the daily friction from repetitive motions starts to damage your joints...  You dont have to give up EQ because of this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarueivywood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darue Ivywood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/14/